keywords enter
---
Syntax: enter <portal>
        enter <exit keyword>

Moves your character through a portal object or a specially named exit.

Portal usage:
  A portal is an object of type ITEM_PORTAL placed in the room. Entering a
  portal teleports you to the destination room stored in the portal's data.
  Some portals are one-way; others allow return travel.
  - Portals cannot be used in rooms flagged as NO PORTAL.
  - In anti-magic zones, there is a chance a portal explodes when entered.

Named exit usage:
  Some doors or passages have keyword names beyond the standard compass
  directions (north/south/east/west/up/down). You can pass through these
  using 'enter <keyword>' instead of a directional command.

Examples:
  enter gate        -- Enters a portal or passage named "gate"
  enter vortex      -- Enters a portal object called "vortex"

See also: recall gate travel portal
